article.headline: Jacksonville 77, SC-Upstate 74
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- Glenn Powell and Delwan Graham each had double-doubles for Jacksonville in a 77-74 overtime victory over South Carolina Upstate Monday night, snapping a 13-game losing streak. Powell finished with 14 points and 12 rebounds and Graham had 10 points and 11 rebounds, 10 offensive, as the Dolphins (3-15, 1-6 Atlantic Sun Conference) dominated the boards and the extra session. Jacksonville, which outrebounded the Spartans 45-36, scored overtime's first five points on Keith McDougald's 3 and Russell Powell's jumper. SC Upstate (10-9, 4-3) cut it to one, 75-74, with 23 seconds left but McDougald made both of his foul shots with 18 seconds to go. Ty Greene, whose 3 sent it to OT, missed another with 4 seconds remaining for the Spartans. The Dolphins grabbed 25 offensive rebounds, leading to 22 second-chance points. Torrey Craig had 17 points and 10 rebounds and Greene finished with 20 points for SC Upstate.
